==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Constrict
<hw>Con*strict"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. &
p. p.</pos> <conjf>Constricted</conjf>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Constricting</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[L. <ets>constrictus</ets>,
p. p. of <ets>constringere</ets>. See <er>Constrain</er>.]</ety> <def>To
draw together; to render narrower or smaller; to bind; to cramp; to
contract or cause to shrink.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Such things as <qex>constrict</qex> the fibers.</q>
<rj><qau>Arbuthnot.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Membranous organs inclosing a cavity which their contraction
serves to <qex>constrict</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>Todd &
Bowman.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Constricted</ent>⟦br⟧
